# UI Component Standard: Shadcn/UI

All UI components must be built on **Shadcn/UI** primitives. Do not hand-roll
buttons, inputs, dialogs, selects, toasts, or other interactive elements from
scratch with raw Tailwind.

## Install a component before using it

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
# Examples:
npx shadcn@latest add button input textarea select dialog toast badge
```

Installed components live in `components/ui/` and can be customised freely.

## Usage patterns

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hand-rolled button
<button className="rounded-lg bg-blue-600 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-white ...">
  Save
</button>

// ✅ GOOD — Shadcn primitive
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
<Button>Save</Button>
<Button variant="destructive">Delete</Button>
<Button variant="outline" disabled={isPending}>Cancel</Button>
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hand-rolled input + label
<label className="block text-sm font-medium ...">Email</label>
<input className="border rounded-lg px-3 ..." />

// ✅ GOOD
import { Label }  from "@/components/ui/label";
import { Input }  from "@/components/ui/input";
<Label htmlFor="email">Email</Label>
<Input id="email" type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" />
```

## Accessible patterns

- Always pair `<Input>` / `<Textarea>` / `<Select>` with a `<Label>`.
- Use `<FormMessage>` from `components/ui/form` for validation errors when
  using React Hook Form; use a plain `<p className="text-sm text-destructive">`
  for manual forms.
- Use `<Dialog>` for modals, `<AlertDialog>` for destructive confirmations.
- Use `useToast()` + `<Toaster>` for transient feedback, not `alert()`.

## Theming

Colours are CSS variables in `globals.css` (`--primary`, `--destructive`, etc.).
Prefer Shadcn variant props over ad-hoc Tailwind colour overrides:

```tsx
<Badge variant="destructive">Superadmin</Badge>   // ✅
<Badge className="bg-red-600 text-white">…</Badge> // ❌
```
